# Phase 70: Dr. Amanda Mistral — Hybrid Architecture & Merge Protocol

## What Changed

Dr. Amanda Mistral's adapter architecture was stress-tested with 16 simultaneous adapters at various merge scales. Catastrophic failure occurred at 16 adapters (scale 0.3) — recursive identity looping. Systematic testing isolated the stable configuration: five core adapters at 0.3 scale. The domain-knowledge adapter (7,451 pairs) caused looping or personality dilution at all tested scales (0.15, 0.05, 0.02). A bulk persona expansion experiment (249 pairs) produced inferior results compared to the original 26-pair handcrafted persona adapter.

A new hybrid architecture was designed: personality and core knowledge remain in LoRA weights; all factual domain knowledge moves to a ChromaDB RAG pipeline; a simple keyword classifier routes queries between the two systems.

## Why

The 16-adapter merge attempted to combine five proven adapters with 11 specialty adapters (arts, military, legal-engineering, etc.) and a massive domain-knowledge adapter (7,451 pairs). The cumulative drift from base weights was estimated at ~4.8x the intended shift, causing latent space collapse and the "mycelium — CADMIES — Dr. Amanda Mistral" identity loop.

Prior sessions (035, 036, 037) established that simultaneous merging at scale 0.3 works for small, focused adapters. This session proved that the same method fails catastrophically with too many adapters or adapters trained on factual exposition rather than voice.

The hybrid architecture addresses a fundamental finding: fine-tuning is the wrong tool for injecting factual knowledge. It overwrites personality and causes instability. RAG separates knowledge storage from voice, allowing each to be optimized independently.

